  <span id="freeText1029582191966469307" style="display:none">The good news is that the same brilliant author who wrote this unbelievably mish mash farce of a novel, 4 years later wrote one the greatest novels of all time, The Grapes of Wrath. This short book(thank, God) is only 207 pages in paperback and for some reason, has an AWOL Mexican Army Corporal show up with a baby that soon dies. The symbolism is lost on me as the rest of the novel has them drinkng enough wine to sink the Titanic. Really disappointed in this one but if Steinbeck wrote a bad novel, that gives me inspiration to me to write a book.<br />One final note, the movie starred Spencer Tracy and Hedy Lamar which is really a puzzler as there is no leading lady part in the novel so I ask my fellow Goodread friends-has anyone seen Tortilla Flats and what did you think of the movie?</span>
