<span id="freeTextContainer11824868089734639975">52nd book of 2020.<br/><br/>This one took me a while to get into, but I enjoyed the second half. It&apos;s certainly not the best Steinbeck, but it is an early work, after all. The idea is great, Danny and his motley crew and their adventures, but the way it&apos;s told is a little too detached for my liking; there is quite a lot of &apos;telling&apos;, which makes the prose uninteresting at times. It&apos;s a fun read, but nothing special. </span>
  <span id="freeText11824868089734639975" style="display:none">52nd book of 2020.<br /><br />This one took me a while to get into, but I enjoyed the second half. It's certainly not the best Steinbeck, but it is an early work, after all. The idea is great, Danny and his motley crew and their adventures, but the way it's told is a little too detached for my liking; there is quite a lot of 'telling', which makes the prose uninteresting at times. It's a fun read, but nothing special. </span>
